VRonald DeVore is involved in a spectrum of applied areas of mathematics, however his core research is in approximation theory. He has applied methods of approximation to the development of numerical methods for partial differential equations, including a recent emphasis on families of parametric partial differential equations and related areas such as inverse problems and parameter estimation. DeVore has been a major contributor to signal and image processing including the areas of compressed sensing and data assimilation, and he was one of the original developers of wavelet compression methods. Two characteristics of his work are nonlinear methods and high dimensional problems. Additionally, he has been a major developer of adaptive methods for solving partial differential equations and greedy algorithms in signal processing.Ronald DeVore is involved in a spectrum of applied areas of mathematics, however his core research is in approximation theory. He has applied methods of approximation to the development of numerical methods for partial differential equations, including a recent emphasis on families of parametric partial differential equations and related areas such as inverse problems and parameter estimation. DeVore has been a major contributor to signal and image processing including the areas of compressed sensing and data assimilation, and he was one of the original developers of wavelet compression methods. Two characteristics of his work are nonlinear methods and high dimensional problems. Additionally, he has been a major developer of adaptive methods for solving partial differential equations and greedy algorithms in signal processing.Ronald DeVore is involved in a spectrum of applied areas of mathematics, however his core research is in approximation theory. He has applied methods of approximation to the development of numerical methods for partial differential equations, including a recent emphasis on families of parametric partial differential equat